=head1 DESCRIPTION

This script imports blocked domain entries from external CSV sources
(e.g., government blocklists) into Sauron-managed RPZ (Response Policy Zone)
zones. It supports:

=over 4

=item * Configurable CSV column mapping

=item * Automatic filtering by removal date

=item * Multiple sources from single or multiple CSV files

=item * Incremental updates (add/modify/delete)

=item * Dry-run mode for testing changes

=back

=head1 CONFIGURATION FILE

The configuration file is in JSON format and defines:

=over 4

=item * Source definitions with CSV file paths and column mappings

=item * Filters for selecting relevant entries

=item * Target zone and CNAME targets for each source

=item * Global settings

=back

Example configuration:

{
  "sources": [
    {
      "name": "mfcr-hazardy",
      "csv_file": "/path/to/blocking_lists.csv",
      "csv_columns": {
        "domain": "URL",
        "date_added": "DATUM_ZAPISU",
        "date_removed": "DATUM_VYMAZU",
        "source": "ZDROJ",
        "dataset": "NAZEV_DATOVE_SADY"
      },
      "filters": {
        "source_regex": "Ministerstvo financí"
      },
      "zone": "rpz.cesnet.cz",
      "cname_target": "*.poker.cesnet.cz."
    }
  ]
}

=head1 EXAMPLES

# Process single source
./import-blocklist --config blocklist.conf --source mfcr-hazardy

# Process all sources with dry-run
./import-blocklist --config blocklist.conf --all --dry-run

# Verbose output
./import-blocklist --config blocklist.conf --source sukl-leciva -v

